<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="783" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/638.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Buckner</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your January 2. Mr. Farnham, National City Bank, informs Department that
                            article 4, loan agreement, bottom page 8, and same article bottom page
                            12, application assigned revenues, would give Clark authority to pay
                            from customs collections back pay and necessary running expenses armed
                            guard.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>